Violation: the mhd_assert(0) in the default branch uses a constant controlling expression. The assert macro typically expands to a selection (e.g. if(!(expr)) ... or (expr) ? (void)0 : __assert()), so with expr == 0 the controlling expression is invariant (constant). This constitutes a Rule 14.3 violation (invariant controlling expression).
